inn1.comm: fullish outside off, moving away, driven to extra cover off the front foot
fullish, just outside leg, tries to clip it fine, misses and is called a wide, opens the account
two in a row, but this one just clipped the pads on the way to the keeper, the umpire didn't hear it though, so too bad for Anderson
short of a good length on the off, coming in a touch, tries to whip it square, clips the thighs and they sneak a leg bye
on middle and off, appeared to hold its line, got his body nicely behind it and tapped it towards mid-off
too straight, worked away between midwicket and mid-on for a single
too short, too wide and gets the treatment, Anderson gifts Watson and he accepts it gleefully, smacking it off the back foot between cover and point for a boundary
good comeback, played inside the line, expecting it to move in a little but it didn't , just escaped the outside edge as he tried to play forward
starts with a wide....down the leg side, the umpire gets some exercise
horrible stuff, so far at least, down the leg side for the fourth time this match, we're just in the second over, another wide, miles from the batsman
rubbish, three in a row, slightly short but the line is still the same, the keeper's being made to work for his pay
gets it right, finally and the crowd roar sarcastically, just on a good length outside off, defended confidently down to cover
a touch shorter, Paine gets forward and dabs it in the direction of extra cover
on the stumps this time, rooted to the crease is Payne who waits, closes the face and turns it to midwicket
beaten this time, tempted him into playing the drive, was full and wide and Paine's eyes lit up, just went at it hard but with almost no foot movement, it swung back in to beat him through the gate
much better from the batsman this time, picked the length early and rocked back to defend it towards the bowler
came back in just a little, waited and guided it behind point for an easy single
fullish outside off, driven firmly to cover
closer to the stumps, not quite driving length, gets to the pitch and blocks it towards cover
full and straight on the off stump, drills it back to the bowler who reacts well on his follow through
back of a length, width and he's not able to time it well, chops it wide of MOrgan at point who dives to his right and saves a couple of runs
shaping in from a good length outside off, decent pace too, 143.1 kmph, defended with an open face to Morgan again
swinging in, Watson is guarded, getting to the pitch and presenting the full face while defending with bat close to pad
short of a good length on middle and off, gets back and drops it in front of cover
nicely done, getting it to leave the right hander, some late movement there, Paine watched it all the way through, opening the face at the last moment to defend it to point
in the zone for the right hander, full and wide, meaty, juicy, Paine is tempted and he crashes it through the covers for a boundary
waits for it, it's slightly short, guides it down wide of Anderson at third man, and he returns a strong throw to the keeper much to the appreciation of this capacity crowd
tight line this time, probing him on middle and off, is well forward is Watson and he blocks it to cover
back of a length this time, rocks back and taps it past the bowler
lands on a good length on the off stump, defended with a bit of a reach towards cover
back of a length on middle, moves back and turns it down towards midwicket

got him! Chopped it on! Short and wide, went for the cut, the shot was on but a bit of inward movement did him in ultimately, a thick inside edge straight onto middle and off to give England their first breakthrough
trying to catch him plumb but the movement's not there this time, full on leg stump, trying to get it to move away a little but it holds its line, plays it awkwardly to cover
gets forward and punches it towards cover point
appeal for a catch, beaten as the ball held its line and he played for the movement into him, the bat clipped the pad and the fielders were excited for a bit, the umpire had no doubts though
beaten! Impressive stuff, left Paine just as he prodded at it from the crease, missed the edge by not much
slightly short on middle, gets on the back foot and defends it short of cover
short of a good length outside off, glides it down to third man for a single to give Ponting the strike
Sidebottom's down-the-leg side woes return, and with a bang as the diving Prior can't get his hands to it, five to the total
measured bowling this time, got the line right, just outside off and Ponting covered it well, moving forward and defending it with a straight bat
wristy, tried t surprise him with the short one but that's Ponting's favourite zone, got forward and swiped it behind square for a boundary
shot off the pitch after landing on a good length, Ponting checked his shot by taking the bottom-hand off
shortish on middle and off, gets back and works it down to mid-on
not fully in control there, banged in short on middle, was a little late in getting into position for playing the hook, got the top-edge over the keeper for four
pushes him back again, is nicely behind it this time and defends it cautiously towards cover
played it nicely in the end, neat stuff, was a little surprised by the bounce but played it really late, tapping it down towards third man from the crease for a single
elegantly done but there wasn't much timing to it, leant into the drive, playing it straight to extra cover
back of a length but he is committed to playing on the front foot, defends it to cover
slightly short on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler from the crease
gets on the back foot and drops it short of point, Ponting calls for a single but Paine sends him back, rightly so
the odd bounce again, was moving in as well, struck Paine hard on the glove as he played forward, trying to tap it into the off side
leaving him this time, got all the way back and defended it to Sidebottom
thrashed through the off side, full and wide and gives him the treatment, creaming him through point
shortish on middle and leg, works it down to square leg, no run on offer there
fullish outside off, swinging in, takes it on the half-volley and drives it through cover and point for a couple of runs
much more confident from Ponting this time, but straight to point, sliced it a little as well, so was uppish but fell short of the fielder
coming back in from a good length outside off, defended down to midwicket
getting it to come back in fairly consistently, gets forward and pushes it to cover
pitched up outside off, lethargically drives it down to point

gone! A hint of frustration as he had middled the last few balls but didn't find the gap, Anderson had set it up, hurled it short on middle, Ponting pulled it away disdainfully but straight into the palms of Sidebottom positioned perfectly at fine leg, two down
shortish on middle, defended with a closed face down towards midwicket
poor ball but gets away with it, Paine pulls it straight down to Sidebottom at short fine leg
angling in from wide of the crease, takes a couple of steps and steers it to point
a touch too straight, worked between square leg and short fine for a single
pitched up on middle, pushed off the front foot to cover
overpitched but the batsman is new to the crease and therefore a little cautious, defended down to midwicket
classy, not overpitched but he just leant into it and eased it past cover point and extra cover for a boundary, crisply struck
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and blocks it towards the bowler
short of a good length on middle, defended from the crease into the off side wide of cover
fuller but he opts to play it off the back foot, presenting the full face back to the bowler
thrashed through point but there's cover in the deep, pitched up and he cashed in, not quite, just a single
appeal for lbw, not a strong one though, pitched outside leg, moved in and struck Hussey high on the pads while he was playing it off the back foot, the umpire was unmoved, you can't give those out
misfield, Strauss the culprit, sets a bad example as he dives to his left and allows it through the gate all the way to the boundary wide of mid-off
the crowd cheer as he stops this one, didn't have to move though, driven straight to him and firmly
lands on a good length just outside off, defended solidly off the front foot wide of the bowler
on middle and leg, worked away wide of midwicket for a single

chance of a catch, cut back in from a good length outside off, Hussey got forward to defend, wasn't quite there to the pitch, was surprised by the bounce, got an inside edge onto his pads and it lobbed up in front of Prior who tried his utmost but couldn't reach it as he dived forward
fullish outside off, driven straight to mid-off
another chance of a catch, Prior's being made to work, short and wide, cut back in, went for the cut, got a thick edge past the diving Prior, he stretched fully to his right but couldn't reach
a touch fuller, gets forward and defends it wide of Bresnan
angling in towards middle, overpitched, driven back to the bowler
slightly short on middle, turned away to midwicket off the front foot
slower offcutter, kept low as he went for the cut, was into the shot too early, didn't pick it
angling in towards middle, defended from the crease back to the bowler, decent start for Bresnan
Hussey's off, is handed a full delivery on the pads and he drives it into the deep through midwicket for a couple of runs
trying to suck him into the drive, but Hussey's measured, easing it to mid-off
full again, driven just wide of mid-off, scampers through for a single and Anderson pulls off a dive to keep them down to that
bowled at 120.4 kmph, gets forward and punches it down to extra cover, thinks of a single but it's not there
Anderson's doing it for England in the field today, it's driven firmly past him, through the line wide of mid-on but he runs and hurls himself to his left to just allow them one run
full and straight, cracked to mid-off, not in the gap, straight to the fielder
Paine's looked good, wasn't a bad ball at all, just a fraction overpitched and he's onto it, square-driving it through point for a boundary
guarded approach this time, similar delivery but he opts to defend it down to extra cover
cutting back in, same result, pushes it down to extra cover
poor delivery and it costs him, too straight, straying on the pads, just a slight shuffle from Paine who glances it down elegantly to the fine-leg boundary
driven on the up towards extra cover, gaining in confidence is Paine
tries to chop it behind point but mistimes it towards extra cover

Hussey's still a little restrained, he's not going after the bad balls, this definitely was one, full and wide, drove it firmly but not really with the intention of getting a boundary, was well stopped at short cover, just a single
countering the offcutter by getting well outside the line and presenting the straight bat
beautifully picked, spotted the slower one, planted his foot forward, took it on the half-volley and cleared long-off comfortably with an effortless swing
pushed through to mid-on off the front foot
well played Mr.Paine, short and wide, guided down to third man to reach his second ODI half-century
appeal for lbw, tossed it up outside off, it spun back in sharply and caught Paine on the pads as he tried to work it past midwicket, was struck outside the line
short outside off, spun back in, he let it be
threw it up outside off, lands full, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
drifting in towards the left-hander, he's coming round the wicket to Hussey, eased wide of point for a single
poor delivery from Swann, it's full and wide, Paine reaches forward and reverse-sweeps it well wide of short third man for four more
pushed it full outside off, covered the turn by stepping outside the line, closing the face and turning it down to midwicket
full outside off, driven hard but straight to mid-off
defends with bat close to pad, held its line this time, straight on middle, a little risky from Hussey who managed to get his bat down in time
short outside off, tried to force it past point but didn't time it well
well fielded by the guy at short cover, driven firmly towards him but he gets a hand to it diving to his left and deflects it to mid-off to allow just a single, much to Hussey's frustration
lands on a good length just outside off, defended watchfully just wide of cover
closer to the stumps, cuts in, dabs it to point
fullish outside off, driven down to a slightly deepish mid-on for a quick single
tossed it up on the off stump, got front and across and clipped it down to short fine
defended off the front foot just wide of extra cover
closes the face and works it down to midwicket
threw it up on the off stump, charged down the track, took it on the full and drilled it down to long-on
slightly short on the off, rocked back and bunted it down to deep cover for a single
guided behind point from the crease and sets off for a quick single
the offcutter again, tries to guide it down to third man but fails to make contact
back of a length on middle, rocks back and turns it off his hips behind square for a single
back of a length on the off, dropped it off the back foot smack in the middle of cover and point for a single, the fielders are undecided as to who should pick it up
miscue and a misfield, pitched up outside off, tries to clear mid-off but ends up slicing it just short of deep extra cover, it bounces over him and he allows them to come back for the second
overpitched on middle and off, leans forward and taps it just wide of extra cover
slightly short on middle, moves back and defends it down to midwicket
lands on a good length outside off, eases that wide of cover for a quick single
slightly short on the off, tries to drive on the up past cover but ends up getting a thick inside edge towards midwicket
slower one, Paine waits for it and runs it down to third man for a single
beaten! Shot away from a good length on middle and off, Hussey was rooted to the crease and tried to work it in the direction of midwicket, was fortunate he didn't nick that one
scratchy again, played inside the line to that one and got a thick edge down to third man for a couple of runs
appeal for stumping, full, much quicker through the air, Paine tries to dig it out, misses, Prior collects well and takes off the bails but he never left the crease
held it back this time, bowled flat, turned down to midwicket
flighted, lands full on the off, chips it just wide of a diving Anderson at midwicket, a single taken
vintage Hussey, that should get him going, low full toss on middle from round the wicket, leans forward, bends low and paddles it down to the fine-leg boundary
drifting in towards middle, drops it just wide of point to sneak in a single, sensible stuff

almost had him! Far quicker and Paine was late onto it, full on the off stump, he attempted to heave it over midwicket, got his bat down just in time to get a thick inside edge down to short fine, nice variation from Swann
short of a length outside off, chopped down to third man for a single
short of a good length just outside off, driven on the rise to cover
Bresnan saw the batsman give him the charge and dropped it short, helped o its way down to fine leg for a single, Paine adjusted well to the change in length
signs of confidence from the left-hander, comes down and crunches Bresnan down to deep cover
short and wide, cut away down to point, can't get it past him
does so this time, beautifully timed, it's never power-play from Paine, latched on to a short one this time and cut it hard behind a diving point to beat third man to the ropes
full on the off stump, driven down to long-off for a single
pitched up on the off, clanked down to long-on
short on middle, Hussey rocks back and punches it to long-on
full and straight, worked away down to deep square leg
quicker through the air, Hussey was late to spot it, tried to chop it down, got a thick inside edge in the direction of square leg
short on the off, punched off the back foot to extra cover
slower delivery, taken on the full and driven to long-on for a single
back of a length outside off, guided down to third man, this partnership has now grown to 74 and a fair pace
lands on a length on middle, driven through the line to mid--on
angling in towards middle, bowled at 137.2 kmph, opened the face just a touch to defend it towards point
cramping him for space there, sticking to a tight line is Bresnan, driven straight to him
nicely done, a bit more power in that shot, similar delivery to the previous one but Paine forced it down the ground past the bowler and mid-off, managed a couple as long-on cut that off
Swann's caught the Sidebottom bug, hurls it down the leg side, gifts a run
shortish on middle, covers it well and defends it into the off side
Hussey's trying hard here, a determined knock thus far, hurled short and he catches the length early, pulling it away over midwicket for a welcome four
pushed wide of the bowler towards mid-on for a quick single
Paine does well, guides it wide of short third where Bresnan returns a strong throw to the non-striker's end but Paine blocks his view, running right in front of the stumps to complete the run
fullish outside off, pushed through to cover
bang on middle, tickled to square leg for a single
full and wide, creamed through to deep extra cover for a single
punched off the back foot down towards cover, is unable to pierce the off-side field
short and down the leg side, tries to help it down on its way to the fine-leg boundary but makes no contact
punished! Short again and he ensures he doesn't waste the opportunity this time, gets forward and pulls it contemptuously through square leg  for a boundary
good running, pitched up outside off, driven hard between long-off and deep extra cover for a couple more
well done, keeps the strike by striking it down to long-on for a single, 10 off the over, they're picking it up now
flighted outside off, gets to the pitch and drives it back to the bowler
wristily done, turned away through midwicket from outside off for a single
angling it in towards middle, defended between point and cover with the intention of squeezing a single and he gets it
short on the off stump, turning in, rocks back and nurdles it wide of midwicket for one more
Hussey's gradually finding his form, normally a busy cricketer he returns to his known ways by reverse-sweeping that wide of short third for a boundary
shortish on middle, gets on the back foot and works it behind square
full on the off, driven down to long-off, one more
back of a length on the off, dropped down to point from the crease
pitched on a length on middle, drilled down to long-on for a single
full outside off, the workmanlike Hussey makes room and drives it wide of deep extra cover for a couple more
pushed back to the bowler and Bopara does well on his follow through, bending low and stopping it to his right
cheeky but third man is finer than normal, late-cut it delicately behind the keeper, had to settle for a couple as Mascarenhas cut that off moving to his right
overpitched and Paine pulls off a stylish drive but straight to short extra cover
a hint of movement into the batsman, walks through while pushing it to the same fielder yet again
slower one this time, lands on a good length on middle, picked it and dealt with it respectfully, defending it back to the bowler
too straight, however, worked away through midwicket into the deep for a single, thought of a second which was on but there was too much calling and indecision out in the middle, from Hussey
tight line on middle, Hussey watches it closely on to his bat and drops it on the off side
closes the face while getting forward and pushes it to midwicket, decent return from the initially wayward, curly-haired Sidebottom
Paine's in prime touch, short outside off, cut away behind point, again, not too much effort but got the timing right, third man had no chance
short of a length on the off, dropped it into the off side with soft hands and ran through for a single
short and wide, attempts a similar shot as Paine but  not fully in control, chops it down, mistiming it to point
short of a length on middle, worked away off the back foot to midwicket
nicely done by Bopara who hurls it in the blockhole, dug out comfortably by Hussey towards extra cover
short of a length outside off, pushed off the back foot to cover, good comeback after that first-ball four
Paine picks the gap, had eyed that space between fine leg and deep square leg, moved across and clipped it stylishly off his pads for four more, he's into the 90s now
two more, full outside off, steers it hard wide of point, deep point runs to his left and cuts it off
back of a length, a slower one, on middle, is struck on the hips as he tries to turn it square, manages a leg bye
fullish, comes down the track, closes the face and turns it to midwicket
swinging in, thumps it down to long-on for one more
angling in towards middle, Paine moves to 96 with a work off the hips behind square
lands on a good length outside off, just a hint of reverse, tries to force it wide of cover, mistimes it
full and wide, driven down to deep cover for a single
well run, Bresnan's a little deep at mid-off, Hussey just punched it towards him and was off in a flash
Paine does the same to Sidebottom, just eased off the front foot, inching towards a maiden ODI ton
comes down the track, knocks it between point and cover and steals another run
slightly short, waits and taps it down to point, there's no run on offer
dispatched for six! Exquisite timing, lands on a good length on middle, comes down the track and flicks it well over the outstretched hands of deep midwicket for a six
pushed wide of extra cover for a single to reach is half-century, his 22nd, timely return to his old ways
beaten! Short of a good length outside off, tries to run it down to third man but doesn't get a touch to it
fullish outside off, driven straight to extra cover, a bit of nerves for the young lad approaching a landmark
pushed off the front foot to extra cover again, he'll have to wait
full on middle and off, driven down to long-off, hands Paine the strike
his patience is being tested here, short of a good length outside off, the offcutter, defended down to point, thinks of a single but it isn;t there
worked away past midwicket and the fielder there almost deflects it past Anderson at mid-on, not quite in the end much to Paine's frustration
it builds further, struck sweetly but straight to cover
short on middle, whipped away down to fine leg, finally a run, after eight balls, moves to 99
lands on a good length outside off, steered to third man for a single, Paine has to wait for the drinks break to end before he can reach the milestone
short of a length outside off, punched wide of cover to give Paine the strike
reaches his maiden ODI century with a drive to long-on, Australia's tradition of producing qualify wicket-keeper batsmen continues, raises his bat and the crowd applaud in appreciation
worked away through midwicket for a single
short of a length on middle, turned away to square leg off the back foot
hopeless appeal for lbw, goes for the reverse-sweep but is struck on the pads, a metre outside the line of the off stump
flighted outside off, driven down to long-off for a single
short of a length outside off, guided down to third man, one more
Hussey gets stuck into that one, just a fraction short outside off and he latches on to it, swinging it hard and mighty into the stands over deep midwicket, his 50th six in ODIs
pitched up outside off, driven down to long-off for a single
brings up the 150-stand in style, full outside off, drills it hard, bisects the gap between mid-off and extra cover perfectly
slower one this time, didn't pick it well, was early into the shot, mistimed a drive to extra cover
straight on middle, whipped firmly but straight to midwicket, still, 12 off the over
flat on middle and off, defended to point off the front foot
full outside off, eased through to deep cover, one more to the total
threw it up outside off, tries to knock it past over, takes it on the full, gets a thick outside edge wide of point
full outside off, bunts it down to deep cover for a single
sees him come forward and alters the length, short outside off, punched down to long-on for a single
quicker through the air on middle, defended into the leg side off the back foot
well kept by Prior, Paine had made room to force that through the off side but missed and Prior hurled himself to his left to save four byes
Paine's down! Nasser Hussain throws a cliche - "Pain for Paine", was bowled short and it came on to him too quickly, went for the pull and was struck hard on the ribs
chasing him outside leg stump again, tries to help it past the keeper but Prior's done well, threw himself towards the ball to keep it down to just one
beaten! Cut away after pitching on a good length on the off, Hussey tried to drive it through the line but was almost done in by the movement
bowled it short seeing him come forward, quick thinking but it's a little too wide and the umpire calls it
down the leg side this time, slower one, misdirected, Hussey gave him the charge and Bresnan made a mess of it
back of a length on the off, cuts it away wide of deep point for a couple more
threw it up just outside off, came down the track and struck it down to long-on for a single

gone! Flatter outside off, takes it on the half-volley and tries to slog-sweep it over deep midwicket but doesn't get hold of it, Joe Denly watches it comfortably into his hands to give England a much-needed wicket
shortish on middle, swipes it down to deep square leg for a single
flattish on the off stump, driven straight to midwicket off the front foot
brilliant fielding by Anderson who throws himself to his left to save the single at mid-on
short and wide, Ferguson gets off the mark with a slash wide of deep point for a couple
goes for the scoop, tries to get it over short fine but is struck on the chest as he tries it out
slower offcutter, drive straight to extra cover

excellent catch by Prior! England are fighting back, the scoring had slowed down and Paine was getting restless, short outside off, goes for the slog over midwicket, gets a thin inside edge and Prior snaps it sharply behind the wicket
full outside off, driven towards point from the crease
lands on a length outside off, run down to third man for a single

picked it up but was really risky, full outside off, clips it over midwicket and for a while it seemed it would go the distance but that wasn't the case, by a mile, landed well short of deep midwicket, just a single
turned off the front foot to midwicket from the crease
driven down the ground to long-on for one
turning in from a good length outside off, gets outside the line to work it square
appeal for lbw, very optimistic, flighted outside off, he goes for the sweep, it turns in and raps him on the pads but he was struck well outside the line
flighted on the off, pushed back to the bowler, good, tight over this
short on leg stump, pats it behind square for a single to keep the strike
driven all along the ground through the covers for a single
driven uppishly wide of short cover into the deep for one more
tight line, lands on a good length on middle, defends it back to the bowler
well struck, short of a length, rocked back, stood tall, he's tall anyway, and punched it hard to beat the gap between long-off and deep extra cover
waited for it and opened the face at the last moment to guide it down to third man
stump-to-stump, worked away towards deep midwicket for a single

got him! Swinging it back in, lands on the off and nips back and Ferguson was surprised by the movement, tried to fend it away into the leg side, got an inside edge onto the pads and then onto the stumps, timely wicket for England
...and is off the mark in style, full outside off, leans into the drive and crashes it wide of mid-off for a boundary
nips back in again, rocks back and defends it to the bowler
back of a length on the off, punched down to cover
four more, errs in length there, short and wide, Hopes just had to find the gap, placed it perfectly off the back foot between point and cover
cover has been pushed back and Hopes just cracks it to him in the deep to keep the strike, mixed results for Anderson in his new spell
short one on middle and off, makes way and drops it down towards point
good length outside off, moves away and pushes it wide of mid-off for a single
White launches into that one, it's the slot, full and wide and dispatches that over extra cover for a boundary
another one, pitched up, poor length, White waits and drills it past Sidebottom and mid-on for four more
low full toss outside off, it's difficult to get those away, pushed to cover, one more to the score

edged and four, didn't deserve that did Sidebottom, full on the off stump and got it to move away, Hopes tried to work it through the leg side, got a thick edge well wide of the keeper to beat third man to the ropes, 14 off that over
getting it to move back in, defended watchfully by White
straying on middle and leg, closes the face and turns it wide of midwicket for a single
mistimed the short one there, was bowled slower, tried to pull it past mid-on but didn't do it well, just a single
full toss bowled at 140.4 kph on the off stump, crunched just wide of mid-off for a single
smacked away, another full toss but this time Hopes takes full toll, smashing it wide of Denly at deep extra cover for a boundary to bring up the 250
that's a bunt, short on the off stump, stays rooted to the crease and pulls it away over midwicket for four
pitched up on the off, tries to dismiss it over mid-on, gets a thick inside edge down to short fine for a single
yorker on middle, just manages to dig it out in the leg side, scrambles a single
full toss on middle, driven down to deep midwicket, will be disappointed he didn't get that away for more
another full delivery, makes room and thumps it to long-off for one more
that was coming, length ball, in the slot, he;s doling out freebies and White gets under it, lofting it cleanly over long-on for a big one
good comeback, in the blockhole on middle, dug out back to the bowler
full outside off, thwacks it down to long-off for a single
poor delivery, slower one bowled short on middle, begging to be hit, White pulls it comfortably in the vacant gap behind square leg for four more

didn't get hold of it but there are plenty of spaces in the outfield, full toss on middle, pulled away in the direction of deep midwicket for a one bounce four, Anderson's figures have been scarred in a matter of a couple of overs

But he contains the damage somewhat with a wicket! Not the best of deliveries, though, another full toss and White miscues the pull, the shot was on but it caught the top edge and Denly took a simple catch at extra cover
struck off the meat but straight to cover, Hopes won't be too happy
full and wide, smacked wide of cover for a quick single
...but it makes no difference to Hopes, overpitched, he makes room and cracks that wide of a diving long-off for four more
slower one bowled short outside off, slapped to cover for a single
swinging in and strikes him on the pads, bowled full but would have missed leg, struck on the toe actually

run out, it's been Anderson's day in the field, in the blockhole, dug out towards long-on, they try to come back for the second but Anderson hurls in a strong throw, what's more it's accurate, knocking out the bails at the non-striker's end to find Lee short of his ground
pitched up outside off, drives it neat and clean down to long-off
yorker length on middle, pushed wide of the diving Bresnan towards long-on for a single to take the strike for the last over
good delivery first up, leaving the right hander, trying to edge it past the keeper, misses, but they sneak in a bye
and that's why, low full toss on leg stump, just chips it wide of deep midwicket, rolls over the ropes, just about
but he's gone this time! Had made too much room and Sidebottom threw in a low full toss outside off, Hopes had to reach for it and ended up chipping in straight to Strauss at extra cover
enterprising stuff, it's Siddle who's pulled off the scoop and Sidebottom's ego is hurt, pitched up on middle, walks across and paddles it over short fine for four
slower one on middle, whipped away through square leg for a couple more, swift running, six to get to 300 now
pitched up on middle and leg, driven hard wide of deep midwicket for a couple

inn2.comm: starts with one bowled full on the off stump, waits and defends it into the leg side

gone! Strauss is surprised by the bouncer, gets his bat and glove away from it, evades the bouncer but the ball brushes the shoulder on the way to the keeper, the umpire Asad Rauf takes his time and then raises his finger, turns out it's the wrong call, an early setback for England
Lee oversteps, full on the off stump, driven to mid-on, time for a freehit, he overstepped
slower one, the legcutter, short, long hop, Bopara makes room and swings it away over midwicket for a boundary, the crowd breaks out in a rapturous roar
good length outside off, swinging away from the right hander, left alone to the keeper
back of a length on the off, hitting 150 kmph, punched off the back foot to extra cover
full outside off, just a push through extra cover and cover point for a couple of runs
starts off with a wide, too wide, given, well outside off
short of a good length on middle, moves back and defends it into the leg side
probing line outside off, Denly is not tempted, leaves it be, he's taking no risks at this stage
excellent shot, pitched up outside off, was in the slot, got forward and lofted it clean and straight over mid-on for his first boundary, came off the middle
bowled on a good length outside off, got to the pitch and square drove it just wide of Hauritz at point who pulled off a good save diving to his right
struck sweetly, full outside off, and he leans into the drive but straight to the fielder at mid-off
fullish on middle and off, pushed wide of mid-on for a single
back of a length on middle, gets back and defends it towards midwicket on the leg side
pitched up on the off stump, pushed wide of extra cover
shaping in on middle, drives it from the crease towards mid-on
full on the off, looks to drive it past the bowler but doesn't time it all too well, pushed back to Lee
slower one this time, the offcutter, got on the back foot and dropped it on the leg side
short of a length on the off, drops it short of cover to pinch a quick single
fullish on the off stump, driven back firmly but straight to the bowler
teasing him with a full length, eased just wide of cover for a single
lands on a good length on the off, defended into the leg side towards midwicket
full outside off, steered down to point where Hauritz dives to his right to stop that one, just a single
inside edge, short of a length outside off, tries to punch it off the back foot away from his body, gets a thin edge past the keeper, who gets a glove to it, down towards fine leg for a couple
angling in towards middle and off, plants his foot forward and defends it to the bowler watchfully
testing him outside off, just a hint of away movement, defended off the front foot towards cover
full outside off, presents the full face while driving it past Lee but straight to mid-off
short of a good length on the off, pushed from the crease to cover
banged in short on middle, latches onto it, rocks back and pulls it hard past midwicket for a boundary
working up some good pace, bowled at 148.8 kmph, pushes him back, it's short of a good length, defended solidly back to the bowler
full outside off, driven back uppishly towards Lee, it lands just short, he gets his hands to it and deflects it just wide of the stumps at the non-striker's end, Bopara was struggling to get back
lands on a good length outside off, pushed firmly wide of cover for a single
cutting back in from a good length outside off, drops it onto the pitch
slightly short on the off, punched from the crease to extra cover
short of a good length on middle, blocks it short of mid-on and sneaks a quick single
probing him outside off, defends it wide of extra cover, thinks of a single but is rightly sent back
kept a little low after pitching outside off, had to bend low to defend it towards mid-on
landing it on a length on middle, driven through the line to mid-on
just getting it to shape away from the batsman, punched to mid-off from the crease
back of a length on the off, rocks back and plays it down on the pitch
too straight and too full, on middle and leg, Denly flicks it away through square leg, no chance for fine leg to race around and cut that off
back of a length on the off, cracked standing tall wide of extra cover but Hussey didn't let that through
nipping back in a touch from a good length outside off, dropped into the leg side towards mid-on
fullish on middle, turned away through square leg, it;s in the gap, Hopes gives chase it drags it back but they've run three
edged and just short of slip, sucked him into the drive there, came back in a hint, went for a blazing drive through cover but got a thick edge, just short of White
banged it short on middle, tried to work it off the hips but didn't make contact
beauty! Full, just outside off, went after it but played inside the line, no movement there, held its line and just escaped the outside edge
short of a good length outside off, pushed towards cover from the crease
edged again, full on middle and he got some away movement this time, Denly tried to drive it past midwicket but the movement produced a thick outside edge, rolled down to third man for a single
full outside off, leant into the drive and played it to cover
that's disappeared! The frustration was setting in with some dot balls but Denly has seen it off, charged down the track, took it on the half-volley and dispatched it into the crowd over long-on
pushing at it away from his body but is surprised by the bounce, Paine keeps well snapping that o his right
short of a good length outside off, pushed down to cover from the crease
a touch fuller this time, gets to the pitch and defends it into the off side
cutting in from a good length outside off, defended off the back foot to the bowler
sharp fielding by Watson at mid-off, driven hard past the bowler but he dived to his left to prevent a couple of runs
back of a length on the off, slaps it back to the bowler
lands on a good length on middle, pushed wide of midwicket
pitched up and he drives but again, he can't get it past Watson at mid-off, didn't time it well either, just a single
angling in towards off and middle, gets to the pitch and blocks it watchfully back to the bowler
short of a good length on middle, dropped into the leg side
slower one cutting in from outside off, dropped short of point for a quick single
short outside off, run down to third man for a single, the crowd, muted for much of the day, is gradually picking up its chirping now
short of a good length outside off, bends low and pinches another single down to third man
Denly attempts a similar shot this time but ends up chopping it down to point

Denly has to go back! Lands on a good length outside off, came down the track to take it on the half-volley and loft it over mid-off, didn't get to the pitch nor did he connect it well, got far more elevation than distance and Brett Lee did a good job taking a few steps back, maintaining a still head and watching it into his palms
back of a length outside off, guides it down to third man for a single
fullish outside off, gets front and across and pushes it down to mid-on
kept low there, cut back in, Bopara didn't get his bat down in time and Paine did well behind the wicket to get his body behind it
played it really late, it moved back in and he dropped his hands to place it behind point for a single
slightly short on the off, moves back and pushes it back to the bowler, tried to punch it past cover but the bat turned in his hand there
angling in towards middle, a pretty big backlift for Prior, taps it down towards mid-on
he's cautious, just short of a driving length, played towards extra cover
slightly short on the off, works it just behind square for a single
back of a length outside off, deceived by the slower one, was into the shot too early there, went for the pull
pitched up on middle and off, driven hard back to the bowler who fields it well on the follow through

worked wide of midwicket where Ponting collects and returns a strong throw to the keeper's end, Bopara, trying to complete the single, just manages to make it in, had to dive to make his ground there, would have been close had that hit
beaten by the legcutter, played inside the line to that one and it just evaded the outside edge
back of a length outside off, cracked off the back foot between mid-off and extra cover for a couple of runs, 50 up for the hosts
short of a good length on middle, turned into the leg side through square leg for a single
comes back in and Bopara is cramped for space, gets an inside edge onto his pads
full outside off, the slower one there, driven crisply but straight to extra cover, the pressure builds
slightly short on middle and off, dropped into the off side short of point, calls for a single and Prior responds, they complete it easily
lucky for Prior, landed on a good length on middle and leg, tried to defend it into the leg side, got a thick inside edge that beat the short-fine fielder to the ropes
short and wide down the leg side, not a good return for the bowler in his new spell, Paine fumbles behind the stumps to concede a bye

run out, Ponting stikes! Pushed off the front foot to extra cover, Bopara sets off but then decides against the run, does so quickly and Prior, who's backed up quite a bit turns to get back to the non-striker's end, Ponting collects, takes aim and scores to find Prior inches short of his ground
lands on a good length outside off, cuts in towards the right hander, defended off the back foot short of point, Hauritz runs in and prevents the single but slips while doing so
fullish on middle, Owais, with a still head, defends it solidly in front of the bowler
slightly short on middle, pulled away to deep square leg for a single to get off the mark

run-out, Ponting, you beauty! Short on middle, dropped short of the Australian captain at midwicket, a suicidal run considering his accurate aim, Ponting picks up and throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end to find Bopara miles out of his ground
short of a length on the off, defended to cover, not risking a single this time
drawing him forward with a good-length delivery just outside off, defended solidly to cover
fullish, just a fraction outside off, pushed down to mid-on
back of a length on the off, punched to extra cover off the back foot
fullish outside off, pushed off the front foot wide of mid-off for a quick single
cut back in, Owais was rooted to the crease and he dropped it back onto the pitch short of the bowler, another miserly over comes to an end
shortish on leg stump, turned away towards deep square leg for one more
they sneak a single as Owais drops it between extra cover and point
just a fraction short on middle and off, defended to extra cover
slower one pitched up on leg stump, Morgan looks to clip it over the leg-side field, gets a thick outside edge through point for a single
hurling it towards middle, holds its line this time, defended back to the bowler
gets across to work it past midwicket but the length isn't quite right, he adjusts and checks his shot, playing it back to the bowler
short of a length outside off, gets towards it to cut it past point, it shoots away and he misses
shortish on the off, guided off the back foot for a single to third man and the crowd breaks out into a naughty cheer
angling it towards middle and leg, a turn of the wrists and a single wide of midwicket
fullish outside off, drives at it, gets a thick outside edge down to third man for a single
full outside off, driven into the ground straight to extra cover
short of a good length on middle, tickled down to fine leg for a single
quicker through the air, short on the off, punched off the back foot wide of long-off for a couple
flighted outside off, slog-swept down to deep square leg for a single
slightly short outside off, turns away, slapped down to deep cover for a single
turned in sharply from a good length outside off, Owais came forward to defend, got a thin inside edge onto his pads, managed a single
altered his pace there, flighted on middle and leg, defended into the leg side
shortish on middle and leg, nudged down to short fine leg
slower one bowled well wide of the off stump, the umpire restrains himself there
slower one, the offcutter again, guided down to third man past the keeper for a single
angling it in towards leg stump, tickled through square leg for a single
picked it up well, waited for it to cut away and smacked it through to deep extra cover for a single
back of a length on the off, drops it down with soft hands wide of point for a single
slower one bowled full outside off, drilled hard past the bowler towards mid-off for a single
pitched up outside off, smites it down to deep midwicket for a single

appeal for lbw, tossed up from round the wicket on leg stump and it turned back in to rap him on the pads as he tried to reverse-sweep that past short third, close shout but replays indicate there was some contact with the bat there. There was also a question of bounce, world have probably gone over
chance of a catch, a very difficult one there, full and wide, bowled really quick, went for the drive, got a thick edge between keeper and slip for a boundary
threw it up on middle, Morgan got into position early and reverse-swept it hard and wide of point for a boundary
tossed up outside off, cracked through the off side for a single into the deep, 10 off the over
fullish outside off, swipes it down to deep midwicket for a single
driven off the front foot wide of mid-off for one more
lands on a good length on middle, gets across and defends it back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, runs it down to third man for a single
slower one bowled short on the off, dropped it into the leg side in front of the ball, just one stare at each other was all that was required and they stole a single
pushed off the front foot down towards long-on for a single
tossed up outside off, pushed wide of cover for a single
threw it up outside off, took it on the half-volley and drove it hard with a flourish between deep extra cover and long-off for four
appeal for stumping, sucked him into the drive there and cleverly held back the length, Owais missed and was almost bowled through the gate, Paine took off the bails but Owais' foot never moved
gets a thick inside edge as he tries to defend off the front foot, rolls down to midwicket
flighted outside off, drilled hard into the ground back to the bowler
spun back in sharply from outside off, Owais was cramped for room, defended it with bat close to pad onto the pitch
short of a length outside off, charges forward and cuts it past point for a couple to reach three figures

five down! Lands on a length outside off, Morgan tries to clear extra cover there, wasn't a great deal of intent in that shot, ended up slicing it straight to Hussey at deep point who held on to a simple catch
short on the off stump, defended off the back foot onto the pitch
the offcutter bowled on a good length outside off, gets across and turns it back to the bowler
fullish on the off, driven down to long-off for a single
beaten by the slow offcutter, went for the drive, it was pitched up but it cut away to just escape the outside edge
spun in from outside off, had to reach for it as he tried to drive it to cover
misdirected, down the leg side and Paine, who had done well so far, concedes more as he fails to get his body behind it
short of a length on the off, punched to extra cover
full on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
flighted outside off, flays it through the off side but to extra cover
turning in from a good length outside off, kept a little low, defended wide of silly point
drives it off the front foot to extra cover again
fullish outside off, eased through to deep extra cover for a single
pitched up on middle, driven hard but straight to midwicket
good length on the off stump, holding its line this time, defended to extra cover
overpitched on the off stump, drilled straight to extra cover
pitched up on middle and off, taps it down to extra cover off the front foot
a single, finally, and the crowd yell, one of many sarcastic cheers we've heard today, all reserved for the home team, pushed down the ground to long-off
tossed up outside off, cracked down to mid-off
oversteps, freehit time, swept down to deep square leg, a marginal call that
in the blockhole on middle, all he can manage is a single to long-on

appeal for a catch, flighted outside off, tried to guide it behind point, replays show that the ball flicked the back of the bat on the way to the keeper, but there was no way it would have appeared so to the naked eye, the bowler didn't go up, only the keeper
swept down to deep square leg
Owais plays the sweep this time, placing it behind square for a single to keep the strike
Owais makes room and Hopes sticks to middle stump, cut down to point

another wicket! Full outside off, had made room, his eyes lit up and he tried to clear mid-off but that was mistimed and it landed straight into the hands of Watson there stationed exactly for such a shot, only a matter of time now
swinging in towards middle, defends it with a straight bat back to the bowler
lands on a good length on middle, turned down to midwicket
fullish outside off, tries to drive it through extra cover, gets a thick inside edge down to fine leg for a single
back of a length outside off, punched into the gap between extra cover and long-off for a three runs
low full toss outside off, Bresnan paddles it down to fine leg for a single
finally, Mascarenhas frees his arms, tossed up outside off, takes it on the half-volley and slog-sweeps it into the stands behind deep midwicket
threw it up outside off, gets to the pitch to play it into the off side, gets a thick inside edge down to midwicket
flat, lands on a good length on the off, defended into the leg side
tossed up outside off, driven to extra cover
turned in towards middle from a good length outside off, pushed back towards the bowler
short of a good length outside off, tries to cut it hard past point, gets an inside edge down to the keeper
angled in towards middle, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
cracks it from the crease wide of extra cover for a single

bowled'im! Not very often that you see it happen, straying on middle and leg, Mascarenhas shuffles across to work it through square, it clips the bottom of the thigh pad and then crashes into the stumps, seven down, Australia inch their way to a 6-0 lead
full outside off, driven down to deep cover for a single, Swann's off the mark, batted well in the Ashes
the slower offcutter, defended from the crease towards point
full outside off, tries to drive it through the line, gets a thick inside edge towards midwicket
swinging in, a bit of reverse there, dug out wide of point for a single
full toss on the off stump, pushed wide of extra cover where White dives and recovers to throw it back to the non-striker's end, they're not letting their guard down even now
short and wide, cut away over point, wide of third man, for a couple
cracking shot! The best of the England innings, overpitched outside off, he gets forward and thwacks it through the covers
pushed through wide of extra cover this time for a single
slightly short on leg stump, fends it away into the leg side for a single
good length on the off, coming in just a hint, defended to extra cover
slower one on middle and leg, tries to work it square, brushes the pads and they sneak a single
back of a length on middle and off, run down to third man for a single
fullish outside off, eased through to deep point for a single
banged in short on middle, pulled behind square towards fine leg for a single
a welcome boundary, short and wide, cut away over point, well wide of third man, for a one bounce four
an inswinging full toss on the off, driven straight to mid-off
tries to play the upper cut this time, the shot was on but came onto him a little too quickly
angling it on the pads, tries to force it past midwicket, can't but salvages a leg bye
short and wide, tries to prod at it off the back foot, misses, it's a no-ball, he's overstepped, so the third freehit of the innings coming up
gets four, low full toss outside off, there to be hit and Swann obliges, stroking it hard through the covers
short of a good length on the off, defended short of cover for a single
back of a length on middle, pushed wide of cover
slower one bowled short on middle and leg, made room and dropped it in front of the bowler on the off side

missed run-out, Ponting's missed it this time, pushed off the back foot towards him, he pulled off a sharp stop and had plenty of time to take aim and throw down the stumps at the striker's end but didn't strike his target
slower one bowled short outside off, tried to chop it behind point, didn't make any contact
pitched up outside off, flayed through the covers for four, plenty of width on offer there and he was on to it in a flash
slightly short on middle, punched back past the bowler, midwicket runs around to cut it off and save the single
pitched up on the off stump, driven down to deep cover for a single
full on the off, pushed through to extra cover
slower one bowled full on middle, swatted down to mid-on for a quick single
short outside off, chipped over extra cover into the deep for a couple of runs

got him! Slowed it down even more this time, and it held its line as it angled towards middle and leg, Swann tried to drive it through midwicket, missed as he was a little early into the shot and the stumps took a beating
the offcutter bowled at 81 mph, wide enough for the batsman to let it go
angling in towards middle and off, defended back to the bowler
full toss on middle and leg, driven down to long-on for a single
pitches it up outside off, pushed straight to extra cover
short of a good length outside off, left alone to the keeper
lands on a good length outside off, keeping its line, left alone through to the keeper
short of a length, punched back to the bowler from the crease
slower one bowled on a good length outside off, cuts away, tries to drive through the line, gets a thick edge down to third man for a couple
pushed off the front foot towards point
short and wide, slow through the air, cut away straight to point
shortish on middle and off, defended from the crease to cover
short on middle, makes room and cuts it down to third man for a single
cuts back in from a good length outside off, mistimes a cut, goes to midwicket instead, they take a single
short of a length outside off, chopped down to point

the crowd erupts, shortish on middle and off, defended off the back foot short of mid-off, Hopes tries to collect and flip it back to the stumps at the non-striker's end but misses it completely, the ball rolls over towards long-off and the crowd, highly diminished now, enjoy a rare moment of amusement
fullish on middle and leg, swipes it down to deep midwicket
back of a length outside off, the field is in and he pulls it over mid-on for a boundary
short and wide, cut away down to third man for a single
nicely played by Sidebottom, full on middle, turned away elegantly through square leg for a couple of runs

slower one bowled on a good length outside off, nudged wide of the keeper for a single, the keeper throws it to Lee who needless hurls it wide of the stumps at the non-striker's end to concede an additional four runs
full and wide, Bresnan makes room and steers that to deep cover
back of a length on middle, tries to turn it through square leg, is struck high on the pads, a single for the taking
overpitched outside off, drilled down to long-off for a single
full on middle and leg, tickled down to fine leg for a single, 11 off the over
short on middle, a bouncer, goes for the pull, misses, stifled appeal from Paine for a catch, the umpire is having none of it
cleaned him up! Full and  straight on middle, tries to drive it past midwicket, clips the pads and crashes into the stumps, nine down now, too quick for the batsman, that
back of a length on middle, dropped into the leg side from the crease
short of a good length on the off, stays his ground and taps it to point
pushed it a little fuller on leg stump, gets on the back foot and defends it back to the bowler
pitched up on the off, driven through to mid-off
full and wide, moves across and crashes it on the bounce to mid-on
full on middle, dug out towards midwicket from the crease
short on middle, guides it down to third man for a single

missed run-out, slower one bowled full on middle, struck down to deep midwicket, calls for the second, Bresnan commits but he's sent back at the last moment, the throw rolls down to Lee who fails to collect, had he done so, Bresnan was out by a mile,. sloppy stuff
short of a good length on the off, defended to extra cover
all over! Fast and furious from round the wicket on the off stump, Anderson has no answer to that one, can't bring his bat down in time and hears the death rattle!
